article.headline: Princeton 40, Lafayette 38
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Kevin Thomas scored a career-high 25 points and Marcus Brown added 18 for Georgia State, which shot 62 percent from the field in its home opener, an 85-78 victory over Louisiana-Lafayette on Monday night. The Panthers (2-2), who shot 72 percent in the first half, led 63-61 with 8:48 to go. They then made 15 of their final 16 free throws. Tiras Wade had 17 points for Louisiana-Lafayette (2-2), while Chris Cameron and Brian Hamilton each scored 15. Hamilton had eight rebounds. Thomas was 5-for-7 from 3-point range and 8-for-8 from the free throw line. Brown made all six of his free throws. Louisiana-Lafayette, which had 19 offensive rebounds, got within 78-76 with 1:52 to play, but Georgia State went 7-of-8 from the line to seal the victory.
